# The Mantras · the words that save you

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of The Mantras](the-mantras.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (The Mantras's organic-form embodiment): the-mantras.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** The Mantras — Faxanadu's password-save system — Gurus give Mantras that store rank, inventory, and respawn church; the distinctive quirk is that a Mantra resets your Golds to a fixed, rank-based amount rather than keeping your total

**what —** Faxanadu's password-save system — Gurus give Mantras that store rank, inventory, and respawn church; the distinctive quirk is that a Mantra resets your Golds to a fixed, rank-based amount rather than keeping your total

**where —** FAX · Faxanadu — Hudson Soft, NES 1989 (Famicom 1987; Falcom's Xanadu line)  Framework inputs: Faxanadu; the World Tree; Eolis; the Mantras; the card-keys; Golds & Ranks  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** They are the memory of the run carried as a spoken word: the line you write down so death is not the end — though it always costs you your purse.

**how —** Crystallized from Faxanadu (NES 1989) — Famicom Xanadu, on Falcom's licensed Xanadu name.

**◌ the mythos —** They are the memory of the run carried as a spoken word: the line you write down so death is not the end — though it always costs you your purse. a being of the World Tree and the climb to the Evil One

**the moniker —** ⟦The Mantras:FAX:ddb67e⟧ · spoken *styl-zex-kreind*

**the seal —** the words that save you

